{
  "_comment": [
    "The exact whisper.cpp CLI sidecar ANVIL ships, keyed by target. Single source of truth for",
    "scripts/fetch-whisper.ps1 (windows-x86_64) and scripts/build-whisper-macos.sh (macos-*).",
    "The target string is format!(\"{}-{}\", std::env::consts::OS, std::env::consts::ARCH).",
    "",
    "whisper.cpp is run as a SEPARATE PROCESS (whisper-cli) and is never linked into ANVIL. It is",
    "MIT (whisper.cpp + ggml, (c) The ggml authors) - cleanly redistributable in an MIT app.",
    "",
    "WINDOWS (windows-x86_64): the plain CPU release build ('whisper-bin-x64.zip', no CUDA, no",
    "BLAS) - carries no extra third-party runtime and runs on any x86_64 Windows. whisper-cli.exe",
    "dynamically loads the best-matching ggml-cpu-<arch>.dll at startup, so ALL CPU variants ship.",
    "",
    "MACOS (macos-aarch64 + macos-x86_64): whisper.cpp v1.9.1 publishes ZERO macOS release",
    "binaries, so on macOS we BUILD FROM SOURCE at the pinned tag - two SEPARATE single-arch",
    "builds (arm64, x86_64), NOT a universal binary (ANVIL bundles per-arch). GGML_NATIVE=OFF (the",
    "default bakes -march=native, non-portable in a shipped binary; OFF gives the portable",
    "baseline and Metal + Accelerate carry the perf). Metal is on by default and the metallib is",
    "EMBEDDED (GGML_METAL_EMBED_LIBRARY defaults ON at this tag) inside libggml-metal - no loose",
    ".metal/.metallib ships. The shared build produces whisper-cli + libwhisper + libggml* dylibs,",
    "staged FLAT with each Mach-O's rpath rewritten to @loader_path (build.sh) so whisper-cli",
    "resolves its dylibs from its own dir env-free; each is re-signed ad-hoc (arm64 needs a valid",
    "signature to exec). binary_sha256 / member sha256s are of THIS host's build (from-source is",
    "not bit-reproducible across toolchains; re-run build-whisper-macos.sh and re-record if the",
    "compiler changes). The release-signing lane re-signs every Mach-O with a Developer ID.",
    "",
    "Unlike ffmpeg, anvil-asr's WhisperSidecar::locate() does NOT hash-check the binary at run",
    "time (whisper is MIT, not LGPL - no licence-control need). These pins are the PROVISIONING",
    "integrity gate (the fetch/build scripts verify every artifact) AND the code-side pin table",
    "crates/anvil-asr/src/pin.rs WHISPER_PINS mirrors them (test `pin_json_matches_the_code`).",
    "",
    "sha256 = RAW file hash (what fetch/build/stage verify). content_sha256 (macOS only, on the",
    "primary binary + every member) = the signing-INDEPENDENT Mach-O content hash: the release lane",
    "Developer-ID re-signs every dylib + whisper-cli, rewriting their raw bytes, so a macOS",
    "bundle-vs-pin check compares content_sha256, not sha256. See crates/anvil-asr/src/pin.rs",
    "macho_content_sha256 (a private copy of anvil-media's parser) + ADR-012."
  ],
